      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TRUE PROMISES (6) stalked the lead then burst clear to score (18.39) at this track in a Grade 5 over 320m. Speedy beginner who can find the front despite the tricky draw. Great chance again. BLITZ (4) was game in defeat with a narrow loss in last time, when a neck second behind Fantasia Queen in 18.37 and posting a new PB this course and distance. Has the ability and looks a key chance. ANJO TOPAZ (3) is a capable type and proved too classy last time to win by 1.75 lengths at this track in a handy 18.41 beating Mr. Snow. Safe beginner who has drawn to advantage. Sure to be thereabouts. LOCO MISS (8) profiles nicely here at this trip.",
